Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation of Solubilities of Asiaticoside in Water, Methanol, Ethanol, n-Propanol, n-Butanol, and a Methanol + Water Mixture from (278.15 to 343.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of asiaticoside in water, methanol, ethanol, n-propanol, n-butanol, and a methanol + water mixture were determined over the temperature range from (278.15 to 343.15) K by a static analytical method. The concentrations of asiaticoside in the saturated solutions were analyzed by reverse-phase high-performance liquid chromatography. An N -type curve was found for the solubilities of asiaticoside in the methanol + water mixture. Two empirical equations were proposed to correlate the experimental data, which fit the data well.
